description.narrative: A national cross-sectoral study of adolescent girls' perceptions of the provision of menstrual health and hygiene services in schools was undertaken. The findings should improve planning for MHH services in schools as well as provide an evidence-base for advocacy to improve MHH services in schools. At the request of the Ministry of Health, UNICEF documented Njombe district's accelerated approach to open defecation free status producing a multi-media package of learning materials to enable other districts to replicate Njombe's approach. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
